<paragraph blockId="319.[151,1436,1770,2013]" lastBlockId="320.[199,1437,150,393]" lastPageId="320" lastPageNumber="321" pageId="319" pageNumber="320">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[267,514,1986,2013]" pageId="319" pageNumber="320" pagination="165 - 197" refId="ref368231" refString="Rondani, C. (1850 c) Osservazioni sopra alquante specie di esapodi ditteri del Museo Torinese. Nuovi Annali delle Scienze Naturali e Rendiconto delle Sessioni della Societa Agraria e dell'Accademia delle Scienze dell'Istituto di Bologna, Series 3, 2, 165 - 197, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1850">Rondani (1850c: 171)</bibRefCitation>
identified some specimens of both sexes received from MRSN as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="De Geer" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[1267,1436,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Gonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="319" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[1267,1436,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="319" pageNumber="320">Gonia capitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(De Geer, 1776) erroneously attributed to Meigen. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[774,995,150,177]" pageId="320" pageNumber="321" refId="ref369190" refString="Rondani, C. (1863) Diptera exotica revisa et annotata novis nonnullis descriptis. Eredi Soliani, Modena, 99 pp., 1 pl. [This is the separate that came out before the journal version with a different title, here as Rondani (1864 a)]." type="book" year="1863">Rondani (1863: 14)</bibRefCitation>
examined the single male specimen he had in his private collection “ 
<emphasis box="[523,1146,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="320" pageNumber="321">
Osservato …. l’individuo che mi rimane di quella 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[1076,1146,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Gonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="320" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gonia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
[I observed the remaining specimen I have of that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[472,542,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Gonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="320" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[472,542,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="320" pageNumber="321">Gonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]” and considered it as belonging to a different species, which he named 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Gonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="320" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="320" pageNumber="321">Gonia genei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This latter specimen was sold to the MZUN in 1866 (see p. 13). 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, A." box="[1029,1223,258,285]" pageId="320" pageNumber="321" pagination="13 - 48" refId="ref348459" refString="Costa, A. (1866) Acquisti fatti durante l'anno 1863. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della Regia Universita di Napoli, 3, 13 - 48." type="journal article" year="1866">
<collectingRegion box="[1029,1093,259,285]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="320" pageNumber="321">Costa</collectingRegion>
(1866: 31)
</bibRefCitation>
listed two MZUN specimens numbered “655”. The MZUN also contains a (non-type) female. Therefore, the 
<typeStatus box="[1199,1286,295,321]" pageId="320" pageNumber="321">syntype</typeStatus>
series should be both in the MRSN and in the MZUN. No specimen under the name 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1130,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Gonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="320" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genei">
<emphasis box="[992,1130,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="320" pageNumber="321">Gonia genei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is present in the MRSN (F. Giachino, pers. comm., 
<date box="[467,655,367,393]" pageId="320" pageNumber="321" value="2020-09">September 2020</date>
).
</paragraph>
